  <h2>It’s fun to send secret messages to your friends with Jewelbots! </h2>
  <p>Make sure you pair up with your friends in order to messsage with them. Refer to the “How to pair your Jewelbots” section.</p>
<p>  If you receive a device in child proof plastic packaging, it is advised to complete the <a href="/pages/firmware">Update Firmware</a> step before pairing or messaging.</p>
<div class="video">
  <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/cxUZdo2bC-4?rel=0&amp;showinfo=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
</div>
  <h3><span>1. Make sure your Jewelbots is unplugged.</span></h3>
    <p> This is because pressing the Magic Button while your Jewelbots is plugged will put your Jewelbots into Upload Mode, which is for coding. </p>

  <h3><span>2. </span>Make sure your Jewelbots is on.</h3>
    <p>You can turn it on by pressing the Magic Button. It should light up in rainbow animation mode to show it turning on.</p>

  <h3><span>3. </span>Put your Jewelbots in Messaging Mode by pressing the Magic Button once. </h3>
    <p>Your device should start cycling through the Friendship Colors of friends that are nearby.</p>

  <h3><span>4. </span>When you see the color of the friend you want to message, press the magic button.</h3>
    <p>This means the message will be sent to all the friends who you paired with for that Friendship Color. Meaning if you have two friends with the Friendship Color red </p>
    <p> near by you, both of them will receive that message. If only one of the two are nearby you, then only one will receive the message. </p>

  <h3><span>5. </span>Press the Magic Button to send your message to your friends via vibration taps!</h3>
    <p>You can send different types of vibrations! Press and hold for half a second to send a short tap or press and hold for 1 second to send a long tap. Only you and your friend</p>
    <p>will know the true meaning of a long or short tap!</p>

  <h3><span>6. </span>To send another message, start from step one each time.</h3>

